props.title: Bar OS for real-world venues
props.subtitle: Website + back office for events, bookings, staff, inventory, POS, and comms—built for collectives and nonprofit bars.

props.html:
Everything your venue needs

Critical Infrastructure runs the public site and the back office together.

  • Public pages, events, and announcements
  • Bookings pipeline, artist profiles, and contracts
  • Staff scheduling, roles, and shift swaps
  • Inventory, suppliers, and low-stock alerts
  • Menus, merch, and POS sync
  • Memberships, access lists, and community comms

Self-host it or run it for a network of spaces.

props.title: Built for the people who run the room
props.subtitle: A showcase of what a modern venue stack can do, without corporate baggage.

props.html:
What it is

Critical Infrastructure is a public website, CMS, and operations suite for bars, clubs, and DIY spaces.

What it solves

  • Keep public info, events, and menus in sync
  • Track talent, bookings, door lists, and crew assignments
  • Run inventory, suppliers, and POS from one source of truth
  • Support multilingual communities with local pages

Open-source, self-hostable, and designed for collectives.
